premise_source_doc_sentence: Neuromuscular ultrasound refers to a field in medicine in which ultrasound is used to diagnosis and guide treatment for people with neuromuscular diseases .
Breast ultrasound is also used to perform fine-needle aspiration biopsy and ultrasound-guided fine-needle aspiration of breast abscesses .

Neuromuscular ultrasound in particular is used in the diagnosis of carpal tunnel syndrome , ulnar nerve entrapment , other neuropathies , Charcot-Marie-Tooth Disease , muscular dystrophies , ALS , and other conditions affecting nerves and muscles .

As part of his dissertation , he demonstrated how a multiscaled non-linear neural net could be used for automatic pattern recognition to localize tumors in ultrasound B-scans , and then to access the underlying echo data and then perform a non-linear multidimensional analysis to classify the tumor type .
A type of ultrasound examination to measure tissue stiffness , which is used to detect tumours , is elastography .
